                    <head>Copy-book of Nydala monastery</head>
                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc form="codex">
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support>
                                    <p>
                                        <locusGrp>
                                            <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>
                                            <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>
                                        </locusGrp>
                                        <material>Parchment</material>
                                        <dimensions type="leaf">
                                            <height quantity="270" unit="mm"/>
                                            <width quantity="210" unit="mm"/>
                                        </dimensions>
                                    </p>
                                </support>
                                <extent>
                                    <measure type="leftFlyleaves" unit="folios"/>
                                    <measure type="rightFlyleaves" unit="folios"/>
                                </extent>
                                <foliation>Modern foliation in pencil. </foliation>
                                <collation>
                                    <formula>1(4, lacks 2-4), 2(8), 3(10, lacks 4, 6-10), 4(8, lacks 1-4), 5(10, lacks 5, 8), 6(10, lacks 4, 8), 7(8, lacks 3-4), 8(8), 9(8, lacks 6-8), 10(8, lacks 6-8)</formula>
                                    <p>
                                        <ref target="https://vceditor.library.upenn.edu/project/69fdae496e6f4a0001f9d1ef/viewOnly">VisColl collation</ref>. <locus from="S56" to="S84" scheme="folios"/>: several missing quires at the end, stubs visible. <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107594">Eriksson (1937)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="217" to="218" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl> presents a different analysis of the quire structure. Eriksson's collation is presented in this <ref target="https://vceditor.library.upenn.edu/project/6a10221c6e6f4a0001fa000f/viewOnly">VisColl collation</ref>. </p>
                                </collation>
                            </supportDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>
                                <note>Top left corner, in ink by a modern hand: <quote>A 134 a.</quote>, written over <quote>NKS 1432. Fol.</quote>, which is written in pencil; centre page, National Library stamp; bottom left coner: National Library book label with current signum; lower part of page, in brown ink by a medieval hand: <quote>ombris adde modis modus est x<unclear quantity="4" unit="chars"/>
                                    </quote>.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>
                                <note>Various partially legible phrases by different medieval hands, e.g. top left corner, in ink by a medieval hand: a skull; below: two lines of text beginning with <quote>Decembris mensis facti est peragendum sine pactis?</quote>. </note>
                            </p>
                        </additions>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="true">
                                <p>Medieval binding. Brown leather over wooden boards. 5 double raised bands and endbands. Originally, 2 clasps. Corner and centre pieces with bosses. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, in ink: <quote>A 134a</quote>.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding">
                                        <height quantity="285" unit="mm"/>
                                        <width quantity="230" unit="mm"/>
                                        <depth quantity="65" unit="mm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <condition>Leather worn and colour almost completely worn off on Spine and LCO. Clasps missing. Endband exposed at bottom and missing at top. LCO, wo deep cuts close to the spine.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100081">Sweden</placeName>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100376">Nydala kloster</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, <origDate notAfter="1525" notBefore="1500">16th century, first quarter</origDate>. <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107594">Eriksson (1937)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="221" to="221" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl> argues a date between <date from="1506" to="1508">1506–1508</date>.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Early provenance unknown.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>The manuscript was given by bishop <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102776">Jacob Serenius</persName> to <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/100866">Jacob Langebek</persName> at some point during the second half of the 18th century., see<bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107602">Eriksson (1943)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="78" to="80" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>. The manuscript was then bought from Langebek's estate by the book collector <persName>Peter Suhm</persName> in <date when="1777"/>. Then, in <date when="1796"/> the manuscript was acquired from him by the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100007">Royal Danish Library</orgName>, <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107592">Ilsøe (2007)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="178" to="179" unit="page"/>
                                    <citedRange from="224" to="224" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>At the library the manuscript was assigned the shelf mark <quote>NKS 1432 Fol.</quote>, which can be faintly seen on <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>Transferred from the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100007">Royal Danish Library</orgName> to the<orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004"> National Library</orgName> in <date when="1929"/> as a part of the Swedish-Danish archival exchange program (svensk-danska arkivalieutbytet).</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
